<component type="desktop">
  <id>com.cassidyjames.plausible</id>
  <name>Plausible</name>
  <summary>Simple and privacy-friendly alternative to Google Analytics</summary>
  <metadata_license>CC-BY-SA-4.0</metadata_license>
  <project_license>GPL-3.0-or-later</project_license>
  <description>
    <p>Hybrid native + web app for Plausible Analytics, the lightweight and open-source website analytics tool. This app wraps the Plausible web app in a native UI, integrating better with desktop operating systems. Native features include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Icon in your App Grid, Applications Menu, Dash, Dock, etc.</li>
      <li>Native header bar with buttons for account settings and logging out</li>
      <li>Save and restore current view and size when closed and re-opened</li>
      <li>Two-finger swipe and mouse button support to go back/forward between views</li>
      <li>Cross-desktop light/dark style support for GNOME, elementary OS, etc.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Other features include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Pinch-to-zoom</li>
      <li>Set the scaling with Ctrl+Plus/Minus or Ctrl+0 to reset</li>
      <li>Slimmed down web app UI (no header or footer with external links)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Features coming soon:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Custom domain support (e.g. self-hosted, not on plausible.io)</li>
      <li>Support for opening external links</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
